Hi Eric,

Thanks for your report, and for the XML file.

On Tue, 2006-01-03 at 19:43 -0500, Eric wrote:
> As per the documentation, I am sending the output of ddccontrol for my
> ViewSonic VP930b 19" LCD.  This is run with my ATI Radeon 9800 Pro
> using the 2.6.14.5 radeonfb driver.  The colors are not so good for me
> out of the box...so I really need this to work. What can I do to help
> develop the XML file for this?  Has anyone tried contacting ViewSonic
> for the spec? Maybe they'd be nice...right?  :)

I'll TRY to contact ViewSonic, we will see if they are nice, or not .-)
The big problem is to reach to good person through the support.
NEC/Mitsubishi and Fujistu/Siemens were very good and I had an answer in
a few days, but I have never been able to contact anyone at Samsung...

> Is it safe to try
> playing around with the different controls to see what they are?

Yes, at least if there is no "autodestroy" control .-))) Seriously, I
never had any problem trying all controls to see what they change.

> Is
> there some particular order I should go in?

I think the direction you took when creating the file you put on your
website is good. Please just don't prefix control names with "samsung_",
and if you don't know what a control does, don't create a control tag
for it, just leave it as a comment like this:
<!-- 0xb6: +/3/8 [???] -->
(see SAM01B4.xml for a full example)

Thanks again,

Best regards,

Nicolas

