I plan on purchasing a new Samsung 960BF which is a buttonless LCD monitor.

I plan to use ddccontrol to adjust the monitor, hopefully it is supported.

I also plan on running several Virtual Machines with VMWare or XEN under
my Linux host.

The guest machines will be CentOS, Solaris and perhaps some other Linux
flavors, Windows XP and Windows SBS 2003.


My questions are these:

How will these guest OS's react to the ddccontrol setting I've saved on
the host?

Will I need to install ddccontrol on each Linux VM?

What about the Solaris?

Will I need to install *MagicTune on the Windows machines?*
*Do the monitors save the *ddccontrol configured settings on the
monitors or only in a file on the running OS?

If I boot up from a Knoppix CD do all of my setting disappear?

Is a buttonless LCD monitor a bad idea for a Linux  user?

Has the Monitor just become one of the most problematic devices for
Linux users?


Please help me get a grip on reality.

**



