Also, I have identified some of the controls. No ground-breaking
innovations here, as most of them were already handled correctly
by ddccontrol using the supplied xml file and some of them are still
unknown. There are even ones for which the xml comments tell
something but I was unable to find their effects.
The following part of this report will go through the individual
controls returned by 'ddccontrol -p' along with their effects,
equivalent osd settings, fix recommendations and some other notes.

terminology
--------
concepts I'm going to use in this report:
  trigger: write-only controls which stick to a base value and writing
    a different value carries out some action (such as reset to defaults)
  setting: read-write controls which generally return the last value
    written when read (except for margins/redirecting invalid input)
    these generally map to a monitor parameter such as brightness
  osd control: an option available through the osd menu or otherwise
    using the buttons on the monitor
  osd path: names of submenus and options in the osd menu that should
    be chosen to access an osd control, separated by slashes
    (such as: color/color tone/warm)
  persistent: a setting which keeps its value when the monitor is turned
    successively off and on (using the soft-off button on the front
    panel of the monitor)
  transient: in contrast to persistent, a setting which resets to a
    default value after an off+on combination (i.e. is volatile)
    interestingly, this usually occurs when switching on, not off
    (the monitor can also be queried when in soft-off)
  regular: if used alone, acts as transient (i.e. effects are restored
    during off+on), but if 0xb0/1 (store settings) is called after it,
    but before turning off (or on, I don't know), the new value is saved
    and is restored after an off+on combination
  IR: "Invalid response, first byte is 0x51, should be 0x6e"
    error message, which occurs quite often (so seems valid)
    (mentioned in results above)
  OK: the specified control needs no change
  FIX: needs a minor change in the xml file
  TODO: something more needs to be done

summary of controls
--------

osd controls without corresponding ddc/ci controls:
(or at least, setting them does not modify any ddc/ci controls)

  osd/h-position   (horizontal position of osd, 0-100)
  osd/v-position   (vertical position of osd, 0-100)
  osd/transparency (boolean specifying whether osd is translucent)
  osd/display time (idle time before osd closes, chosen from
                    5 sec, 10 sec, 20 sec and 200 sec)
  information      (tells the horizontal and vertical frequency,
                    screen resolution and 'PP' (which I don't know))

list of ddc/ci controls:
(controls are identified by their hex id and xml name if present)

0x04 defaults
  trigger, base:0, persistent
  1 -> reset default settings
    resets the following settings to these values
    * 0x0e coarse      90/180
    * 0x10 brightness  80/100
    * 0x12 contrast    80/100
    * 0x16 red         32/64
    * 0x18 green       32/64
    * 0x1a blue        32/64
    * 0x20 hpos        50/100
    * 0x30 vpos        35/70
    * 0x3e fine        0/31
    * 0x87 sharpness   15/25
    * 0xe0 colorpreset 0/3
    * 0xf2 gamma       0/2
    (actually it resets all settings, but these were
    the ones I reset before each test)
    it also resets some of the osd settings which do not
    have ddc/ci control equivalents
    * osd/h-position   50 
    * osd/v-position   50
    * osd/transparency Off
    * osd/display time 20 sec
    also sets a 'dirty' flag, so an auto adjustment will be
    performed when changing to a new resolution or turning off+on
    saves settings (as 0xb0/1)
    monitor led turns off for 0.5 seconds
    throws IR
  TODO: IR

0x05 defaultluma
  trigger, base: 0, regular
  1 -> reset brightness and contrast
    resets the following settings to these values
    * 0x10 brightness  80/100
    * 0x12 contrast    80/100
  OK

0x06 defaultgeom
  trigger, base: 0, partially persistent
  1 -> reset geometry settings
    osd path: setup/image reset/yes
    resets the following settings to these values
    * 0x0e coarse      90/180
    * 0x20 horizontal  50/100
    * 0x30 vertical    35/70
    * 0x3e fine        0/31
    * 0x87 sharpness   15/25
    sets the dirty flag (this is a persistent effect)
    (all other effects are regular)
    throws IR
  TODO: IR

0x08 defaultcolor
  trigger, base: 0, regular
  1 -> reset colour settings
    osd path: setup/color reset/yes
    resets the following settings to these values
    * 0x10 brightness  80/100
    * 0x12 contrast    80/100
    * 0x16 red max     32/64
    * 0x18 green max   32/64
    * 0x1a blue max    32/64
    * 0x0e colorpreset 0/3
    * 0xf2 gamma       0/2
  OK

0x0e coarse
  setting, 0-180, regular
  osd path: image/coarse
  sets the clock
  osd value is 1638 + control value (thus, real range is 1638-1818)
  OK

0x10 brightness
  setting, 0-100, regular
