This control is surprisingly not in CAPS string. I forced it to be
enabled.

> 0xe2 UNKNOWN
>   setting, 0-1, persistent
>   this setting is persistent, but doesn't affect others
>   it has to do something with the dirty flag
>   when in state 0, slow auto adjust (0x1e/1) takes approx. 4.5 seconds
>   when in state 1, slow auto adjust (0x1e/1) takes approx. 2 seconds
>   timing of fast auto adjust (0x1e/2) seems unaffected
>   if the dirty flag is turned on (using 0x04 or 0x06), an auto
>   adjustment takes place on the next off+on or resolution change
>   which turns the dirty flag back off
>   if, however, this setting is set to 1 before the off+on or
>   resolution change, the dirty flag is not processed
>   that is, the auto adjustment does not occur and the status of
>   the dirty flag is kept
>   when it is reset to 0, if the dirty flag is on, the auto adjustment
>   takes place on the next off+on or resolution change
>   (it this setting is not reset to 1 meanwhile)
>   TODO: check if it's the real and only effect

I think it is an engineering VCP, so I don't think we need to support it
(not in CAPS).

