When writing non-0 to 0xf0, I got the following error:

Writing 0xf0, 0x04(4)...
Invalid response, first byte is 0x51, should be 0x6e
51 82 01 f0 4c 04 4c ff ff ff ff                | Q...L.L....
Control 0xf0: +/4/4 [???]


I attached the very verbose output, hope it's useful:
ddccontrol pci:01:00.0-1 -r 0xf0 -w 4 -v -v 2&> 1 > magiccolor.out

After writing 4, there appears a lighter area in the top-left corner of
the screen, and the menu shows indeed that MagicZone is activated. 

The menu option selected is OSD->Color->MagiColor[MagicZone]. BTW the
MagicColor submenu has on my monitor the following options: [Off=0,
Demo=1, Full=2, Intelligent=3, Magiczone=4] (numbers verified). 

Furthermore MagicZone has a submenu, with the following 8 settings:
(order as found in the OSD menu)

0xfa Hue[0..100]
0xfb Saturation[0..100]
0xf9 Brightness[0...100]
0xfc Sharpness[0.100]M / [0..20]P
???? H-Pos +/-
???? V-Pos +/-
???? H-size +/-
???? V-size +/-

I tried to figure out which menu option changes which ID, but I only
noticed changes in the dumps for the first 4 options. Note, that 0xfc
(Sharpness) has values [0..100] in the menu, but [0..20] in the
protocol. Changing 40->10 in the menu resulted in 8->2 in the protocol
level... The last 4 values have no numeric feedback in the menu, i.e.
there are no known "bounds" - I guess because it changes with the screen
resolution.

Greg

PS: my sharpness control is also on 0x87, just like on Tamas Hubai's
913V.

