Hi Florin,

Thanks for your report, it is not the first time I have problems like
this with kernel headers (this is one thing that is absolutely not
standardized accross Linux distributions)...

On Wed, 2006-03-08 at 17:56 -0800, Florin Andrei wrote:
> Downloaded ddccontrol-0.4 and I'm trying to build it on Fedora Core 4
> 32bit version.
> I am only doing a test, to see if it compiles at all.
> 
[snip]
> 
> I attached a few files that I thought might be useful to identify the
> cause. Anything else I might try? Just let me know.

Yes. Could you try to apply the attached patch ?
# patch -p0 < ddccontrol-0.4-FC4-headers-fix.patch

Then run 
# ./autogen.sh
if you have the necessary tools, otherwise you can skip this step.

If it works, I will very probably release a new version, as this may
affect many Linux distributions.

Best regards,

Nicolas

