On Sat, 2006-03-11 at 01:06 +0100, Nicolas Boichat wrote: 
> 
> Thanks for the output. The database files are attached.

Cool, thanks! I'll give them a try when I actually start to play with
ddccontrol. I'm still reading the docs.

> There is something really strange with these monitors: they share the
> same PNPid (SGX0200), so ddccontrol can't distinguish between each
> monitor.

Maybe GDM-5411 is just a newer version of GDM-5011P in disguise? They
look fairly different on the outside, but the menus look and behave
quite similar.
They're both Sony, actually. Silicon Graphics just OEM'ed them.

In any case, they're both high-quality monitors, despite the fact that
they've been used and abused a long time.

> I also think SGI GDM-5411 CAPS string is invalid, but I need to be sure
> it is not a bug in ddccontrol. Could you please run this command on the
> GDM-5411 :
> # ./ddccontrol -p -v -v -c

The result is attached.

