Sorry if this comes twice, got a bounce first.

I ran ddccontrol and it told be to send this here, I'm using an nVidia 
6200 something with the 8756 drivers and a Samsung SyncMaster 757 DFX. 
I'll also attach the edid.bin as dumped by nvidia-settings.

The monitor actually has a USB connection for controlling these things and it 
came with a Visual Basic (!) program that controls it. I haven't used that in 
many years and I have no idea what protocol it uses.

The monitor has these onscreen controls
position/size
    position
    size
    zoom
geometry
    parallel/rotation
    pincushion/trapezoid
    pinbalance
    sidepin corner
    pinbalance corner
color
    color1
    color2
    color3
screen
    clear moire
    linearity
    focus
advanced
    degaus
    recall
    video input level (0.7 or 1 volts)
menu
    stuff for configging the osd

