Hi Dmitry,

Sorry for the delay, I've been really busy,

On Thu, 2006-04-06 at 09:34 +0400, mad_soft@...144... wrote:
> On Wed, Apr 05, 2006 at 07:46:54PM +0200, Nicolas Boichat wrote:
> > Hi Dmitry,
> > 
> > Could you please try to add more verbosity to your output (with a
> > command like this:
> > LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol -p -c -d -v -v
> > )
> > 
> > "Invalid response, magic is 0x23" means there is an error in the
> > checksum, it shouldn't happen...
> >
> 
> Goodday!
> 
> Here's the output of LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol -p -c -d -v -v
> I also tried with framebuffer driver and i2c device
> (LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol -c -d -v -v dev:/dev/i2c-2), but still no luck.

Thanks for the detailled output, it seems your monitor has a bug, the
following patch should fix the problem.

Apply with "patch -p0 < patch_file_name" in ddccontrol/src/lib.

It it works, then send again "LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol -p -c -d" so I
could add your monitor to the database.

Best regards,

Nicolas

