Hi David,

Thanks for your interest in ddccontrol

David R Mulligan wrote:
> Sorry I missed Nicolas Boichat's comments on this thread.  I was just
> going through the archives.
>
> Nicolas; if ddccontrol could execute scripts on particular events then
> we could tie ddccontrol into all sorts of things.  I wonder what beyond
> desktop rotation and KVM like functionality people would find to do with
> it?
>   
That a good idea, unfortunately, there is no "event" in the DDC/CI
protocol. We would have to poll a specific control, every 5 seconds for
example. This may be done with a simple bash script (but it would be
rather CPU-intensive as we would have to re-init ddccontrol every 5
seconds). I think we need some command-line interface to do this
(allowing to send get a control value every 5 seconds without having to
re-init the whole library), but, as you may guess, I don't have time to
work on this now.
> Are there PIP and volume control commands in DDC too?
>   
PIP: maybe (but we don't know how to use it)
Volume control: yes (never tested)

Best regards,

Nicolas
