Hello all.

The attached archive contains the output of "ddccontrol -p -c -d"
(0.4cvs05072006 version) for the Sony SDM-S205K in digital and analog 
mode, plus some notes.

The write command 
  $ ddccontrol -r CONTROL -w NEWVALUE pci:03:00.0-1    # or pci:03:00.0-2
works fine and I did a dummy SNY4C00.xml -and SNY4D00.xml- to avoid the error 
messages. After a few tests and reads trying to make a proper xml file for 
testing the gui I concluded that there's far more wisdom here and you'll do it 
sooner and better. :)

I want to use bash scripts, so the gui is not important to me, but I wonder if 
the addition of the xml file, a re-compilation or anything else could improve 
the speed. The above command needs almost 2 seconds in an AMD64 3700 (linux 
i586). Do you have equivalent timings? Has the pci/dev device something to do 
with it?

Anyway, it feels **very good** having the monitor under ddccontrol at last. A 
ton of congratulations and thanks to everybody for your work.

lardhan


