Nicolas Boichat wrote:

> It would be nice if you could play with 0xfd, 0xfe and 0xff controls, as
> I don't know what they do (these are LG proprietary controls).

Hi Nicolas,

These are the missing controls:

		<control id="power" address="0xfd">
			<value id="off"   value="0x0"/>
			<value id="on"    value="0x1"/>
		</control>
		
		<control id="gamma" address="0xfe">
			<value id="-0.5"   value="0x0"/>
			<value id="0"      value="0x1"/>
			<value id="+0.5"   value="0x2"/>
		</control>
		
		<control id="sharpness" address="0xff">
			<value id="0"   value="0x0"/>
			<value id="1"   value="0x1"/>
			<value id="2"   value="0x2"/>
			<value id="3"   value="0x3"/>
			<value id="4"   value="0x4"/>
			<value id="5"   value="0x5"/>
			<value id="6"   value="0x6"/>
			<value id="7"   value="0x7"/>
			<value id="8"   value="0x8"/>
			<value id="9"   value="0x9"/>
		</control>
		
Please notice that the "Power control" is actually a switch to 
enable/disable the power led only (no other functionality, it seems), so 
the name is somewhat misleading; but it's the closest match I found in 
options.xml. Also, it would be nice to make the "sharpness" control a 
list, but adding 'type="list"' attribute doesn't make a change.

Thanks for your work,

Evgeny


