I've been able to install the ATI driver.  I have fglrx, i2c_more, and 
i2c_dev listed amond the lsmod result.  gddccontrol probes without 
result.  I'm running Suse 10.1 (2.6.16.21-0.21), ddccontrol 0.4.2, 
ddccontrol-db 20060730, gtk 2.8.10, ati driver 8.28.8.run, and the video 
card is a x1600 on the pci-express bus.  The monitor is connected 
through the VGA port.  The monitor is a Samsun SyncMaster 193P and 
gddccontrol results in "No monitor supporting DDC/CI available."  I 
suspect its a PCI-express support issue.  The website suggestion I let 
you guys know.  Thanks for all the awesome work.

Paul


