> > Which is right, manual or monitor?
> 
>    Manual is right. It seems that Xorg report videocard's RAMDAC maximum 
> pixel clock.

Thanks.

This DDC software is really fantastic.  We have access to firmware
capabilities without any vendor software.  Thank you from the bottom of
my heart.  I mean it.

One more question on this model.  Does ddccontrol support the "auto
pivot" feature?  (User physically rotates the screen, monitor detects
change, software then does xrandr automatically.)  Is support planned? 
It would be very nice.  The monitor firmware shows an alert when the
user rotates, so it knows and reports what is happening.

Mark

P.S. In case anyone Googles this model, here are first-cut xorg.conf
stanzas for nvidia Linux drivers.  Just use ddccontrol to run the
auto-adjust once, the screen position will lock.

Section "Monitor" # Samsung971p LCD 19" monitor
 Identifier "MonitorLCD"
 ModelName "Samsung971p"
 Option "DPMS" "true"
 DisplaySize 376.32 301.056 # mm
 HorizSync 30.0 - 81.0 # kHz
 VertRefresh 56.0 - 75.0 # Hz
 # pixel clock is 140 MHz max
 Modeline "LCD1280x1024@...235..." 109.62 1280 1336 1472 1720 1024 1024 1026
 1062
EndSection


Section "Device"
 Identifier "NVIDIA NV20 [VisionTek GeForce3]"
 Driver "nvidia"
 VendorName "All"
 BoardName "All"
 Option "hw_cursor"
 Option "RenderAccel" "true"
 Option "AllowGLXWithComposite" "true"
 Option "NoLogo"
 Option "RandRRotation" "true"
EndSection


Section "Screen"
 Identifier "ScreenLCD"
 Device "NVIDIA NV20 [VisionTek GeForce3]"
 Monitor "MonitorLCD"
 Option "RandRRotation" "true"  # nvidia option
 Option "DPI"  "86 x 86" # nvidia option - 0.294 mm pitch
 Option "UseEdidDpi" "false" # nvidia option
 DefaultDepth    24
 SubSection "Display"
  Depth   24
  Modes   "LCD1280x1024@...235..." "1024x768" "800x600" "640x480"
 EndSubSection
 SubSection "Display"
  Depth   16
  Modes   "LCD1280x1024@...235..." "1024x768" "800x600" "640x480"
 EndSubSection
 SubSection "Display"
  Depth   8
  Modes   "LCD1280x1024@...235..." "1024x768" "800x600" "640x480"
 EndSubSection
EndSection


