   I've just tested SyncMaster 206BW and it has the same ID SAM027D as 
the 226BW, so it seems that 226BW initial sample uses firmware written 
for 206BW.

   SAM027D.xml is for SyncMaster 206BW, not 226BW.

Oleg Artamonov wrote:
>   Initial sample. 226BW will be available in retail on March 2007.
> 
>   Monitor has additional MagicBright mode "Dynamic contrast" so it needs 
> to be added to options.xml, control "magicbright":
> 
> <control id="magicbright" type="list" name="Magic Bright Mode" 
> address="0xDC">
>   <value id="text" name="Text" />
>   <value id="internet" name="Internet" />
>   <value id="game" name="Game" />
>   <value id="sport" name="Sport" />
>   <value id="entertain" name="Entertain" />
>   <value id="custom" name="Custom" />
>   <value id="dynamic" name="Dynamic Contrast" />
> </control>
>


